    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-06T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-06T20:00:00-05:00" n="540"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/254b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-06T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 6, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>817. An important telegram is now being encoded to you containing for
                    communication by you at earliest possible moment text of message from the
                    President to the Emperor.<note n="78" xml:id="d540fn78">Telegram No. 818,
                        December 6, 9 p.m.; see <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_784">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 784</ref>, footnote 70.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
